AN 18-year-old Mpumalanga boy has been killed allegedly by his aunt and three other relatives for stealing a T-shirt. Andile Sambo, who was a Grade 10 pupil, at Bhekiswayo Secondary School was allegedly assaulted by his aunt and other relatives at their house in Numbi, outside Hazyview. Brigadier Selvy Mohlala said the incident happened last Tuesday. He said the deceased was allegedly assaulted with a wooden log and sjambok on his head and body. “He was later taken to Phola Nsikazi Clinic for medical treatment. He was certified dead on Wednesday, 25 May, hence the arrest of the trio. “One suspect is still on the run and police are expecting to arrest him soon,” he said Gladys Mashabane (51), Skholiwe Mbuyane (27) and Sandiso Mbuyane (26) appeared in the KaBokweni Magistrates Court today, 30 May. Their case was postponed to 3 June for a formal bail application. Mpumalanga provincial commisioner, Lieutenant-General Semakaleng Manamela, has condemned the incident. She advised parents to lead by example and stop taking the law into their own hands.